Package com.att.aro.pcap

Provides an interface that defines a listener for incoming packets, provides bean classes for handling different types of packets, and provides adapter classes for accessing packet data and the pcap libraries.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    PacketListener
    Defines a listener that is used to listen for incoming packets.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AROCryptoAdapter  
    DomainNameSystem
    Used to interpret DNS information from a packet containing DNS data
    IPPacket
    A bean class that provides access to IP Packet data.
    NetmonAdapter
    Encapsulates the logic used for parsing data from a Microsoft Network Monitor trace file and adapting it for use with the ARO Data Analyzer.
    Packet
    An adapter class for packet data.
    PCapAdapter
    An adapter class that is used to access the Pcap libraries.
    PcapngHelper
    Helper class to check if a pcap-ng file is created by tcpdump tool on Mac OS Maericks
    TCPPacket
    A bean class that provides access to TCP packet data.
    UDPPacket
    A bean class that provides access to UDP Packet data.
